cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.LG

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with device-free localization in IoT environments. It may also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it involves wireless communication and signal processing. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it involves the automation of a calibration process. It may also fall under cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) as it involves the use of crowd-sensing to construct a fingerprint database. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as machine learning techniques may be used to improve the accuracy of the localization.
